annotations.title: NASA's Perseverance rover lands on Mars
NASA's Perseverance rover lands on Mars
NASA's Mars helicopter takes flight as first aircraft piloted on another planet

content.text:
- **February 18, 2021 –** NASA’s Perseverance rover successfully landed in Mars’s Jezero Crater ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/02/18/nasa-perseverance-rover-lands-mars#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Perseverance%20rover%20successfully%20landed,This%20successful)), beginning a mission to search for signs of past life on the planet and collect rock samples for a future return to Earth ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/02/18/nasa-perseverance-rover-lands-mars#:~:text=mission%2C%20Perseverance%20is%20equipped%20with,slated%20for%20launch%20in%202026)).  
- **April 19, 2021 –** NASA’s Ingenuity Mars Helicopter completed the first-ever powered, controlled flight on another planet (Mars) ([www.axios.com](https://www.axios.com/2021/04/19/nasa-ingenuity-mars-helicopter-first-flight#:~:text=NASA%27s%20Ingenuity%20Mars%20helicopter%20made,This%20milestone%20paves%20the)), marking a historic milestone for extraterrestrial aviation and demonstrating the potential of aerial exploration on Mars.
